        {"data": {"id": "26. Subject  to  the provisions of Part VII of this Act, the award made by the arbitral tribunal  shall be final and binding on the parties to the arbitration agreement.        27. (1)  Within fourteen days of receipt of the award, unless another period of time has been  agreed upon by the parties, whether at the request of the arbitral tribunal or otherwise --- or    (a) a party, with notice to the other party, may request  the arbitral tribunal  --   ( i ) to correct in the award any errors in computation, any clerical or      typographical errors or omissions or any errors of a similar nature ;  or        (ii)  to modify the award where a part of the award is upon a matter not referred to  arbitration, provided  such  part can be separated from the other part and does not  affect the", "label": "Chunk"}},
