        {"data": {"id": "Section 12   International Arbitration Act 2020      Page 12  Act 21 of 2020  to      PART 4 – COMPOSITION OF ARBITRAL TRIBUNAL  12  Number of arbitrators  The parties are free to determine the number of arbitrators and failing such  determination, the number of arbitrators shall be three.  13  Appointment of arbitrators  (1)  No person shall be precluded by reason of his nationality from acting as an  arbitrator, unless otherwise agreed by the parties.  (2)  The parties are free to agree on rules of procedure in appointing the arbitrator  or arbitrators, subject to the provisions of sub-sections (4) and (5).  (3)  When failing to agree under sub-section (2) –  (a)  in an arbitration with three arbitrators, each party shall appoint one  arbitrator, and the two arbitrators thus", "label": "Chunk"}},
